description:
IC 1396A also commonly known as the “Elephant Trunk Nebula” is a star forming region some 2,400 Light Years from earth. The bright rim is the surface of the dense cloud that is being illuminated and ionized by a bright, massive star. The Nebula is now thought to containing several very young stars less than 100,000 yr old.  Presented in the hubble pallet also known as SHO which stands for Sulfur-Hydrogen-Oxygen.  I am really happy with the results of this image as this target is rich in all gasses!  Hope you all enjoy and thanks for any constructive comments.

Equipment:
Telescope - Meade 6000 series 115mm APO refractor
Imaging Camera- ZWO ASI 1600mm Pro Cool
Mount - Sky-watcher EQ6-R Pro

Software:
Sequence Generator Pro
Pixinsight
Lightroom
Photoshop

Lights:
SII-60x300sec
HA- 60x300sec
Oiii-60x300sec
Red-30x60sec
Green-30x60sec
Blue-30x60sec
35 Darks
100 Bias

Total integration 16.5 Hours
title: IC1396 the Elephant Trunk Nebula
